##I want to embrace every human being who is suffering

Micro Signal thelivings

The function introduction, reconstructs our life with the narrative beauty.

"It is a misconception that many people think that medical professionals are so used to death and death that they become numb to it and are no longer bothered by compassion and emotion. "

Image courtesy | SIPA

Foreword
It was a war that broke out at the beginning of the new year around every ordinary, ordinary Chinese.
This is our war. We discuss it eagerly, analyze it carefully, deplore the loss of life in the disaster, are moved by the fearless spirit of the healer, and work tirelessly for the little things we can do.
The Sea of life, we walk and cherish.
Netease's "Our war" feature tells the story of how, every day, we meet the epidemic shirtless.

Our War | serialized 12

"My hometown is sick, " Chen Nan posted in a friend's circle on December twenty-nine, but was soon inundated with news of the epidemic and N95 masks, "You can feel that panic spreading through the screen of your phone, " he said.
Chen Nan, a full time psychotherapist who runs a studio in Xuhui District with friends, cancelled her return a few days ago after being dissuaded by her parents. But how can all rest assured, the New Year's eve and called home video phone.
Her biggest worry was her father. My father had high blood pressure and diabetes, the basic diseases that can make a bad situation worse if you get infected. But his father was not care, only complained about the price of food after the city, "He did not want to let me worry. ".
The call lasted 78 minutes, and Chen Nan was repeatedly told by his parents to take extra precautions. Before hanging up, Chen Nan looked at his parents' sad face, his eyes were blurred, he wanted to comfort them, but his brain was short-circuited, his sadness and anxiety came together, he said no more, and finally he simply said "don't go out" .
Pressing the red hang up button, Chen Nan sat on the edge of the bed for a quarter of an hour, waiting for the tears to dry, and checking the time on her cell phone. That's how the year of the boxer began.

These days, Chen Nan can't stop thinking about Wuhan, the place she grew up in, filled with memories of childhood and youth. The Yangtze River, sitting on those old docks, under the moon like mother's hand, soothing childhood dreams.
"The 'premature' of the Wuhan people is a big deal. "
"premature" in Hubei dialect, is to eat breakfast meaning. Her favorite breakfast, in addition to the nationally famous hot-and-dry noodles, there is fuqinghe's beef powder.
On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Chen Nan, armed to the teeth, went to the neighborhood supermarket to buy food. The streets were deserted. "The eyes above the masks were on alert. ". When I opened the door, the woman who lived upstairs was taking out the trash on the ground floor. When she saw Chen Nan, she said, "little girl, your mask is too thin. " Chen Nan nodded to the woman.
Along with the outbreak came panic. "panic spreads faster because emotions can be contagious. " All the information received on mobile phones has to do with the epidemic, with medical supplies in their home towns running short and confirmed cases exploding, the News created a cloud of negative emotions, like an invisible haze, that forced everyone to gulp down.
"If you receive too many messages, it will increase anxiety and panic, " said Chen Nan, who shut down Wechat, uninstalled Weibo and turned off his phone in the afternoon. It wasn't until 8 pm that she woke up from her sleep and hurriedly opened her phone -- as if she'd been urging her family to check in every night.
She was in a foreign land, her closest relatives were in an infected area, bound by fear and depression, " 'doctors can't treat themselves, ' ah, even psychological consultants, but also to face their own psychological crisis, this point can not escape also can not escape, but I still have some ways of self-counseling.
Chen Nan curled up on the bed with her knees in front of her chest and gave herself a "warm hug" with her arms around her calves.
"One thing about people is that they talk to themselves, and I try to calm myself by talking to myself in an acceptable, gentle tone, " she says. More than 10 minutes later, she begins "mindfulness meditation. " "In a nutshell, it's a very stress-reducing meditation that relieves bad feelings. Some people may think it's very complicated, but it's really not that difficult. It only takes 10 minutes. "
At 9 p.m. that night, Chen Nan's partner called, and they finally got a chance to talk about all the things that had been bothering them for days. On the other end of the line, they listened, wept, and helped her unblock the blockage, when it comes to emotional problems, good social support is very important. She and I are best friends and each other's counsellors.
At this time, Chen Nan did not think that one day, he would choose to "actively seek" such pain.

It all started when a longtime client told her about an experience.
The client asked for her help on Wechat, saying it was like a time of war. He settled his wife and children at home, put on a mask, and piled into the supermarket shopping spree, buying enough for a week. Carrying a few extra-large shopping bags, ran to the nearby pharmacy, mask has been out of stock, only bought 2 bottles of alcohol.
When he got home in the evening, he just coughed while having dinner, and when his middle school daughter saw what she looked like, he quickly drew back his body and frowned, in a gruff voice, Berate him: "Dad, you stay away from me! Don't infect me. "
At first, he didn't mind, buried himself in his daughter's dishes. But the daughter moved the bowl away and began to make it worse, constantly blaming him: "Why did you end up wearing only one mask when you were warned to wear two? "? This kind of light blue disposable mask so thin, with the virus can easily break the droplets, if infected, not harm the whole family?"
He felt aggrieved because the masks were in such short supply that his family had only a small bag of them, and he wanted to save one for his daughter.
In the evening, as he sat on the Sofa watching the news, his daughter came up to him and asked, "Daddy, did you wash your hands when you came back from the outside? "
"Of course I did. How can I eat without washing my hands? " He asked his daughter. But the daughter still refuses to forgive, repeatedly asked him whether or not to wash his hands, he was asked bored, with a sullen voice said "washed washed. ".
"Dad you this attitude is guilty, absolutely did not wash. " The daughter looked at him disapprovingly.
"Well, since you said I didn't wash my hands, I'm going to wash them again. "
"What are you washing your hands for now? You could have given me the virus. " My daughter glared at him, turned and ran into the study, slamming the door.
He rushed into the House and gave his daughter a dressing down. At the sound of crying, his wife quickly pulled him out, to help his daughter scolded him: "You usually say that the most beloved daughter, today how willing to vent on her body? "
"I had no idea what was wrong with her, " he said, noting that he was home in the midst of the epidemic, alone on the Remember the Titans, competing with others for supplies, and that he was chilled by the fastidiousness and indifference of his loved ones.
"I don't know why I said so much on wechat today, it really bothers you. " The client half-jokingly asked, "do I have to charge for saying this? "
Seeing this, Chen Nan had to pretend to be relaxed, this is a special time, this situation to deal with special, and is a regular customer, should be free of charge "free clinic" , and then made some advice to him.

Soon after, another friend left a message for her saying that she had returned to her home in Beijing from Hubei Province on January 13. After the outbreak of the disease, "Hubei People" became a mark of shame that could not be torn off, coupled with a high degree of self-sensitivity, and aggravated the anguish of the heart, "My friend is a self-aware person, and when I tried to comfort him, I would ask him to describe some of his feelings in as much detail as possible, to make a 'clarification' , he said of the feeling of coldness and rejection, like in Fang Fang's novel Arrow through the heart. ".
"sometimes it's hard to really understand another person's pain. "
Since then, Chen Nan has been concerned about the plight of her friends: A friend on the phone crying to her boyfriend, who was upset and broke up with her; a classmate making jokes about the outbreak in a group of friends, "inappropriate" by a mutual friend..
Under the pressure of the epidemic, the relationship between people suddenly became indifferent and alienated, everyone became an island, living in a "calm despair. ". Sensitive people become more sensitive, and the seeds of pain planted in the past take root.
Chen Nan came up with the idea of doing good, "if it doesn't do anything, at least I should do something. " .

Before volunteering for the program, Chen Nan posted a blue and yellow picture in a circle of friends with a phone number beginning with 027 in the yellow box.
This picture is from the People's Daily's micro blog on January 24: Wuhan residents can call this free psychological assistance hotline in case of serious psychological crisis.
"027-85844666. " This string of numbers Chen Nan memorized very skillfully, "originally this also called Wuhan Psychological Hospital 'Heart Talk' hotline. ".
After assembling the information, Chen Nan became convinced that it was a problem
There are only six public welfare hotlines in China, including those in Hubei Province (as of January 26) . They are Wuhan, Yichang, Xiangyang, Suizhou, Shiyan and Xiaogan, and most of the hours are from 8:00 a.m. to 21:00 p.m. The other 11 hours are a dangerous gap for those in crisis, and with limited hotline resources, those most in need may not receive timely help.
On January 27, the total number of confirmed cases nationwide was 4,515, nearly tripling from January 24, when the number of cases increased rapidly. Hubei Province confirmed 1,291 cases, including 892 in Wuhan, as well as a surge in panic.
On the same day, the COVID-19 issued the guiding principles for emergency psychological intervention in pneumonia outbreaks, in which front line health care workers and confirmed patients were listed as the first group of intervention, the second level of intervention is for people with mild illness, and the third level is for people related to the first and second levels, such as family members, colleagues, friends and volunteers involved in rear rescue, these three levels of the population are also our priority to help.
That afternoon, introduced by a friend, Chen Nan joined a volunteer psychologist's board of Examiners and, after being vetted, was quickly drawn into a "support network. ". The members of the group belong to the field of "strong soldiers" , most of them hold the second-level consultant qualification certificate, some also have rich on-site psychological first aid experience.
The aid group was on a 24 hour shift, with Chen Nan initially scheduled to be on duty from 9 pm to 7 am. During her shift, she had been waiting in the group to be assigned counseling duties.

"health care workers on the front lines of the epidemic areas are more likely to face psychological crises. "
A smoking doctor told Chen Nan that the patient had left that day, long after they had tried to save him. The doctor felt guilty and wondered if he had really done his best. He wanted to bow as the bed was being wheeled away, but time was not on his side and he immediately turned to the next patient.
That night, the doctor fell asleep with difficulty, wanting to cry but unable to make a sound. Doctors and nurses don't really rest for long, and the next day they face intense work pressure. The more they force themselves to sleep, the more counterproductive it is. The doctor began to fear that if anything should happen to him, the pillar of his family would collapse. He was more worried about whether his family would be in trouble at this critical moment.
"In the face of a major threat, the body and mind will have a corresponding adaptive response, which is the stress response, this consultant is an acute stress response. When it comes to stress, it has three phases: the alert phase, the resistance phase and the exhaustion phase. Resistance period is also the focus of psychological intervention time, but a large part of the health care workers, the degree of stress has reached moderate to severe, serious impact on the work before seeking help.
"The man in white is also a man of flesh and blood. He has his own weaknesses and pain. I gave him two pieces of advice. The first was to take stock of what he thought he was doing well every day. The second was to increase his social support, spend more time with his friends and never criticize each other. "
From the day he became a "volunteer counselor" , Chen Nan was challenged by the heavy workload of counseling, sometimes working the night shift, feeling exhausted and easily overwhelmed by the counselor's negative emotions, causing "vicarious trauma" to themselves.
She was helping a patient's family at 1:30 in the morning. The counselor's relatives are now in a serious condition, can only worry, several people in the family have emotional collapse, Chen Nan accompanied each other crying, at the end of the consultation, her tears still can not stop, "I think of their parents. ".
But a counselor from Hunan Province helped her, and Chen Nan herself had systematically studied psychological first aid, which came in handy at critical moments.

Every day at noon, the first thing Chen Nan wakes up to is to watch the national epidemic of Clove Garden in real time, the face of that "bleeding rooster" , her hometown crowded in the middle of that area, has been red and black, and seems to be in the SCAB.
On February 1, there were 11,791 confirmed cases in China and 7,153 in Hubei Province. Chen Nan made a phone call, just shouted "old Ted and old two" , "the nose got vinegar. " . At this time, even speak a Wuhan dialect, also let a person sad.
At 11:45 that night, she was given a consulting assignment. The consultant, a doctor, said he was "about to give up, " and his voice was Hoarse and he sounded like he had just woken up from a nightmare.
The doctor said he is now preparing to rest, but in recent days, no matter where he is or what he is doing, he still feels like he is still fighting in the isolation ward, and even though he has changed his clothes, he still feels like he is still wearing a white protective suit, wearing an N95 and a clear face mask, he saw all the real scenes being replaced by hospital wards, an image that made him feel extremely depressed, often accompanied by heart palpitations and nausea.
Chen Nan soon realized that the doctor's condition was very serious. In the ward for a long time overload operation, mental stress, emotional nowhere to vent, each other's daily life has been seriously disrupted, resulting in a sense of unreal withdrawal. At this point, immediate psychological first aid is needed to help the doctor get rid of anxiety and restore calm.
During Chen Nan's evaluation and further questioning, the caller repeatedly shouted "hello" due to the poor quality of the call. "Can you hear me? " She said in a calm, soft voice. Chen Nan did not begin "First Aid" until she was sure.
"I heard him talking really fast, so I asked him to try to breathe and slow down. He didn't do very well the first time, but he did better the second time. Then I asked him to describe what he saw, what the ground looked like under his feet, what his surroundings looked like, and what colour he was wearing,"Chen Nan asked him to describe it in as much detail as he could, it's a temporary distraction, a way to reconnect with the present.
His voice trembled slightly, and after describing the window in front of him intermittently, he asked if he had done the right thing, and, with Chen Nan's encouragement, he described the next thing.
"You're doing great. Now slap your knees and use them to feel what it feels like to be slapped, " Chen Nan told him.
Next, Chen Nan teaches the other person to focus on his breathing. However, in the first aid to the next step, the phone was suddenly cut off by the other side, the call lasted only 25 minutes.
Chen Nan immediately called back, and the other person apologized, saying he had just been given a new assignment and needed to get there quickly so he could only come back another time.
Chen Nan urged him, "try not to be alone these days, and spend more time with your companions. "
Then, like a race for time, both sides hung up. Faced with this crisis in counseling, Chen Nan worried: "This psychological first aid is a one-time intervention, mainly to help him help himself, and then he has to rely on himself to improve his mood. "

By 1:15, Chen Nan was on the phone with another counselor. Just answer, the other side paused for a minute, only issued a faint sob, as if just cry. Instead of repeating "hello" to make sure, Chen Nan tried to soothe the other person with a gentle tone, reminding her "don't rub your eyes with your hands. ".
She cried for several minutes, and Chen Nan stayed patiently with her. "when it comes to loneliness, and the need to connect with others, it's important to listen and be there. ".
The consultant was a nurse in Wuhan. Although she was ready when she set off on the first day of the New Year, she was on the verge of breaking down due to the extreme intensity of her work and the oppressive environment beyond expectation, i feel suffocated all the time.
"It is a misconception that many people think that medical professionals are so used to death and death that they become numb to it and are no longer bothered by compassion and emotion. "
After a rare moment of rest, the nurse couldn't sleep. She missed her 5-year-old. Before leaving home, she coaxed the child that she was going on a long trip and would be back soon, telling him to be good and to listen to his father. The child took her by the hand and told her to hurry back. But think of it this way, in the heart that Valve Meng ran to open, tears burst, she was afraid of affecting other people, ran out of the building alone, cried A.
After listening to the nurse, Chen Nan repeated the story in her own words to make the counselor feel "understood and cared for. ". She then asks the person to try a "cognitive adjustment, " untangling negative emotions and preparing for a long-term outbreak.
At last, the man on the other end of the line took a deep breath, and his voice finally calmed down.
"these counsellors are caught in an epidemic storm, they are stressed physically and psychologically, they are in a constant state of stress, they are depleted, they are desperate and helpless, they need rest and they need to be cared for. ".

"front-line health care workers are on the clock all day, if there is a psychological crisis, can they really find time to seek help? " Was the question Chen Nan himself posed to himself.
In the news, doctors in protective suits were so tired that they had to lie down on the ground. A paramedic leaned his head against the ambulance carriage and closed his eyes for a few minutes, "They work very hard and usually take the opportunity to rest. Sometimes they wish they could take a little time for themselves when they are in crisis, but it is very difficult to do that. ".
Among the Health Care Workers Chen Nan is currently assisting, sleep deprivation is widespread, with most showing signs of anger, numbness, sadness, depression, self blame and psychological fatigue.
Faced with ineffective treatment, they often feel worthless, while the family also in the invisible to themselves caused great pressure.
Chen Nan's current goal is not only to provide psychological counseling for those in need, but also to help those in need to practice self help, under the pressure of time
In 2013, for example, the World Health Organization issued a psychological first aid guide for field workers (1) , "which, seven years later, is still a good guide for most health care workers. ".
There is SQR-20 mental health self-assessment questionnaire, can also be used to do some self-screening, "the group of friends to make this self-test form into a small program, the title is done quickly, at most only two or three minutes of time. ".
| Who Mental Health Assessment Questionnaire (image courtesy of respondents)
Most of the counsellors the volunteers contacted were ordinary people affected by the outbreak. "This is understandable. Although the general population is classified as level 4 in the guidelines for psychological intervention issued by the National Health Commission, this population has a larger base and should not be ignored. "

For example, a counselor who was diagnosed with OCD at a mental health hospital a few months before the outbreak told Chen Nan, "this outbreak has made my ocd worse. ".
In the current severe pneumonia epidemic, the consultant thought that he had a very serious "fear Crown" , worried that he was infected with a new coronavirus, so he made a series of seemingly absurd forced behavior as Foshan
During the Spring Festival, he found himself washing his hands more often, from once or twice to six or seven times. Until later, he rubbed his hands red, dried them, and sprayed them repeatedly with an alcohol spray.
He wore three masks when he took out the trash. Adjusting the nose clip, the outside of his thumb touched his cheek, and he was instantly gripped by fear and anxiety that there was a virus on his thumb. When he got home, he panicked, buried himself in the sink, rinsed his face over and over with water, then grabbed the alcohol Tampon with his tweezers and rubbed it as hard as he could.
In Chen Nan's view, this compulsion is in part a way to relieve the anxiety inherent in it. And because of that, compulsive behavior is highly addictive.
The current outbreak for this "mental cancer, " said the disease, is no doubt a blow, it makes the consultant feel "very painful. ".
Because the patient's family simply could not understand his behavior, telling him "not to overthink it. ".
In counseling, Chen Nan instructs the counselor to use "cognitive behavioral therapy, " which replaces the original thought with a positive thought, reminding him that it's the wrong thought when the compulsive thought sneaks up on him or tries to distract him. For example, describe what's in front of you, or do something else. In addition, Chen Nan urged counsellors to stick to a previously prescribed medication.
"ideas can be generated in the brain, which is more powerful than a virus. I repeatedly stressed to him, 'nothing is permanent, everything flows' , when the forced concept comes, let it go naturally, also can use mindfulness inhalation method, focus on their inhalation, try to slow the inhalation rate, but also can use muscle relaxation method, feel the muscle tension, instant relaxation of the kind of warm and comfortable feeling, suitable for the relaxation of the body and mind, but also easy to worry about the crowd

At the same time, there are three groups of people in this fourth group who have urgent psychological problems: The elderly, pregnant women and children, and even if the counseling task is heavy, Chen Nan will give priority to help.
Late in the night of Feb. 3, a counselor came to her for help on behalf of her father. The 73-year-old usually likes to take a walk in a nearby square or sit under an old tree and play the black flute. Now the outbreak of the epidemic broke this peaceful time, the old man shut himself in the room all day, staring at the window daze.
At first, the child does not care, think the father is "in response to the national call" , shut himself at home, but a little boring. Then he noticed that his father was often glum and withdrawn, and it occurred to him that his mother had died in the spring of 2003.
Although the mother is not SARS patients, but now the critical external environment, or can not help but make the elderly sad. At dinner, the children pressed their father, and it was true.
Late the night before, the old man turned on the light, took out the old photos of him and his late wife in the turbulent period, and wiped them again and again with a clean white cloth. He had been depressed for nearly a week.
Since the old man's hearing was poor, the counselor acted as a "setter" , passing key messages between the old man and Chen Nan, "I suggested to the consultant that the old man could do something else at home, play the flute, and let the old man talk about his past, which is a good healing in itself. He also advised him to talk to the elderly, the family is the best psychological support."
At the same time, Chen Nan offers her advice to people who live in segregated homes. During the SARS period, the SARS Comfort Manual (2) compiled by Taiwan's mental health action alliance was very suitable for self-adjustment, for example: List some things that can make you happy, make a "To do" list To implement gradually; Receive News messages within 1 hour each day, to avoid information overload, causing unnecessary panic.

That day, Chen Nan told me that at the end of January, by Chen Nan's father's balcony, other residents were often heard singing in unison. Listen carefully, it is "I and my motherland. ".
When the father heard that "not a moment can not be divided" , the moment can not help, eyes turned, tears for his face. If it was not his mother afraid he was infected, desperately blocked, father really want to join the "Balcony Chorus" team, the isolation of the city after the panic and suffocation, let it out.
"Old Terry has become so sensitive, " Chen Nan said, teasing his mother with a laugh. But on the other end of the line, Chen Nan's own eyes were watering.

Postscript

"At the end of one session, a counselor told me that during the days of isolation at home, he wanted to hug everyone he saw on a TV screen. "
Chen Nan said the remark struck a chord with her. Psychological assistance is to repair the emotional bridge, to help each other out of the psychological crisis of the Black Whirlpool.
In those dark moments when there is no light in sight, people are no longer "depressed and mourning" , rubbing a warm fire in each other's support. To This Day, Chen Nan still insists that one day she will come home, hug her family, "too soon" .
(the interviewee is not his real name)

These days, Chen Nan can't stop thinking about Wuhan, the place she grew up in, filled with memories of childhood and youth. The Yangtze River, sitting on those old docks, under the moon like mother's hand, soothing childhood dreams.
"The 'premature' of the Wuhan people is a big deal. "

There are only six public welfare hotlines in China, including those in Hubei Province (as of January 26) . They are Wuhan, Yichang, Xiangyang, Suizhou, Shiyan and Xiaogan, and most of the hours are from 8:00 a.m. to 21:00 p.m. The other 11 hours are a dangerous gap for those in crisis, and with limited hotline resources, those most in need may not receive timely help.
On January 27, the total number of confirmed cases nationwide was 4,515, nearly tripling from January 24, when the number of cases increased rapidly. Hubei Province confirmed 1,291 cases, including 892 in Wuhan, as well as a surge in panic.
On the same day, the COVID-19 issued the guiding principles for emergency psychological intervention in pneumonia outbreaks, in which front line health care workers and confirmed patients were listed as the first group of intervention, the second level of intervention is for people with mild illness, and the third level is for people related to the first and second levels, such as family members, colleagues, friends and volunteers involved in rear rescue, these three levels of the population are also our priority to help.

A smoking doctor told Chen Nan that the patient had left that day, long after they had tried to save him. The doctor felt guilty and wondered if he had really done his best. That night, the doctor fell asleep with difficulty, wanting to cry but unable to make a sound. Doctors and nurses don't really rest for long, and the next day they face intense work pressure. The more they force themselves to sleep, the more counterproductive it is. The doctor began to fear that if anything should happen to him, the pillar of his family would collapse. He was more worried about whether his family would be in trouble at this critical moment.
"In the face of a major threat, the body and mind will have a corresponding adaptive response, which is the stress response, this consultant is an acute stress response. When it comes to stress, it has three phases: the alert phase, the resistance phase and the exhaustion phase. Resistance period is also the focus of psychological intervention time, but a large part of the health care workers, the degree of stress has reached moderate to severe, serious impact on the work before seeking help.
"The man in white is also a man of flesh and blood. He has his own weaknesses and pain. I gave him two pieces of advice. The first was to take stock of what he thought he was doing well every day. The second was to increase his social support, spend more time with his friends and never criticize each other. "
From the day he became a "volunteer counselor" , Chen Nan was challenged by the heavy workload of counseling, sometimes working the night shift, feeling exhausted and easily overwhelmed by the counselor's negative emotions, causing "vicarious trauma" to themselves.

The counselor's relatives are now in a serious condition, can only worry, several people in the family have emotional collapse, Chen Nan accompanied each other crying, at the end of the consultation, her tears still can not stop, "I think of their parents. ".

"front-line health care workers are on the clock all day, if there is a psychological crisis, can they really find time to seek help? " Was the question Chen Nan himself posed to himself.
In the news, doctors in protective suits were so tired that they had to lie down on the ground. A paramedic leaned his head against the ambulance carriage and closed his eyes for a few minutes, "They work very hard and usually take the opportunity to rest. Sometimes they wish they could take a little time for themselves when they are in crisis, but it is very difficult to do that. ".
Among the Health Care Workers Chen Nan is currently assisting, sleep deprivation is widespread, with most showing signs of anger, numbness, sadness, depression, self blame and psychological fatigue.
Faced with ineffective treatment, they often feel worthless, while the family also in the invisible to themselves caused great pressure.
Chen Nan's current goal is not only to provide psychological counseling for those in need, but also to help those in need to practice self help, under the pressure of time
In 2013, for example, the World Health Organization issued a psychological first aid guide for field workers (1) , "which, seven years later, is still a good guide for most health care workers. ".
There is SQR-20 mental health self-assessment questionnaire, can also be used to do some self-screening, "the group of friends to make this self-test form into a small program, the title is done quickly, at most only two or three minutes of time. ".
| Who Mental Health Assessment Questionnaire (image courtesy of respondents)
Most of the counsellors the volunteers contacted were ordinary people affected by the outbreak. "This is understandable. Although the general population is classified as level 4 in the guidelines for psychological intervention issued by the National Health Commission, this population has a larger base and should not be ignored. "

For example, a counselor who was diagnosed with OCD at a mental health hospital a few months before the outbreak told Chen Nan, "this outbreak has made my ocd worse. ".
In the current severe pneumonia epidemic, the consultant thought that he had a very serious "fear Crown" , worried that he was infected with a new coronavirus, so he made a series of seemingly absurd forced behavior as Foshan
During the Spring Festival, he found himself washing his hands more often, from once or twice to six or seven times. Until later, he rubbed his hands red, dried them, and sprayed them repeatedly with an alcohol spray.
He wore three masks when he took out the trash. Adjusting the nose clip, the outside of his thumb touched his cheek, and he was instantly gripped by fear and anxiety that there was a virus on his thumb. When he got home, he panicked, buried himself in the sink, rinsed his face over and over with water, then grabbed the alcohol Tampon with his tweezers and rubbed it as hard as he could.
In Chen Nan's view, this compulsion is in part a way to relieve the anxiety inherent in it. And because of that, compulsive behavior is highly addictive.
The current outbreak for this "mental cancer, " said the disease, is no doubt a blow, it makes the consultant feel "very painful. ".
Because the patient's family simply could not understand his behavior, telling him "not to overthink it. ".
In counseling, Chen Nan instructs the counselor to use "cognitive behavioral therapy, " which replaces the original thought with a positive thought, reminding him that it's the wrong thought when the compulsive thought sneaks up on him or tries to distract him. For example, describe what's in front of you, or do something else. In addition, Chen Nan urged counsellors to stick to a previously prescribed medication.
"ideas can be generated in the brain, which is more powerful than a virus. I repeatedly stressed to him, 'nothing is permanent, everything flows' , when the forced concept comes, let it go naturally, also can use mindfulness inhalation method, focus on their inhalation, try to slow the inhalation rate, but also can use muscle relaxation method, feel the muscle tension, instant relaxation of the kind of warm and comfortable feeling, suitable for the relaxation of the body and mind, but also easy to worry about the crowd

"front-line health care workers are on the clock all day, if there is a psychological crisis, can they really find time to seek help? " Was the question Chen Nan himself posed to himself.

In the news, doctors in protective suits were so tired that they had to lie down on the ground. A paramedic leaned his head against the ambulance carriage and closed his eyes for a few minutes, "They work very hard and usually take the opportunity to rest. Sometimes they wish they could take a little time for themselves when they are in crisis, but it is very difficult to do that. ".

Among the Health Care Workers Chen Nan is currently assisting, sleep deprivation is widespread, with most showing signs of anger, numbness, sadness, depression, self blame and psychological fatigue.

Faced with ineffective treatment, they often feel worthless, while the family also in the invisible to themselves caused great pressure.

Chen Nan's current goal is not only to provide psychological counseling for those in need, but also to help those in need to practice self help, under the pressure of time

In 2013, for example, the World Health Organization issued a psychological first aid guide for field workers (1) , "which, seven years later, is still a good guide for most health care workers. ".

There is SQR-20 mental health self-assessment questionnaire, can also be used to do some self-screening, "the group of friends to make this self-test form into a small program, the title is done quickly, at most only two or three minutes of time. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
| Who Mental Health Assessment Questionnaire (image courtesy of respondents)

Most of the counsellors the volunteers contacted were ordinary people affected by the outbreak. "This is understandable. Although the general population is classified as level 4 in the guidelines for psychological intervention issued by the National Health Commission, this population has a larger base and should not be ignored. "

At the same time, there are three groups of people in this fourth group who have urgent psychological problems: The elderly, pregnant women and children, and even if the counseling task is heavy, Chen Nan will give priority to help.
Late in the night of Feb. 3, a counselor came to her for help on behalf of her father. The 73-year-old usually likes to take a walk in a nearby square or sit under an old tree and play the black flute. Now the outbreak of the epidemic broke this peaceful time, the old man shut himself in the room all day, staring at the window daze.
At first, the child does not care, think the father is "in response to the national call" , shut himself at home, but a little boring. Then he noticed that his father was often glum and withdrawn, and it occurred to him that his mother had died in the spring of 2003.
Although the mother is not SARS patients, but now the critical external environment, or can not help but make the elderly sad. At dinner, the children pressed their father, and it was true.
Late the night before, the old man turned on the light, took out the old photos of him and his late wife in the turbulent period, and wiped them again and again with a clean white cloth. He had been depressed for nearly a week.
Since the old man's hearing was poor, the counselor acted as a "setter" , passing key messages between the old man and Chen Nan, "I suggested to the consultant that the old man could do something else at home, play the flute, and let the old man talk about his past, which is a good healing in itself. He also advised him to talk to the elderly, the family is the best psychological support."
At the same time, Chen Nan offers her advice to people who live in segregated homes. During the SARS period, the SARS Comfort Manual (2) compiled by Taiwan's mental health action alliance was very suitable for self-adjustment, for example: List some things that can make you happy, make a "To do" list To implement gradually; Receive News messages within 1 hour each day, to avoid information overload, causing unnecessary panic.

That day, Chen Nan told me that at the end of January, by Chen Nan's father's balcony, other residents were often heard singing in unison. Listen carefully, it is "I and my motherland. ".
When the father heard that "not a moment can not be divided" , the moment can not help, eyes turned, tears for his face. If it was not his mother afraid he was infected, desperately blocked, father really want to join the "Balcony Chorus" team, the isolation of the city after the panic and suffocation, let it out.
"Old Terry has become so sensitive, " Chen Nan said, teasing his mother with a laugh. But on the other end of the line, Chen Nan's own eyes were watering.

Postscript

"At the end of one session, a counselor told me that during the days of isolation at home, he wanted to hug everyone he saw on a TV screen. "
Chen Nan said the remark struck a chord with her. Psychological assistance is to repair the emotional bridge, to help each other out of the psychological crisis of the Black Whirlpool.
In those dark moments when there is no light in sight, people are no longer "depressed and mourning" , rubbing a warm fire in each other's support. To This Day, Chen Nan still insists that one day she will come home, hug her family, "too soon" .
(the interviewee is not his real name)
